  29:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  30:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Enable the RTC domain access.
  31:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Configure the RTC Prescaler (Asynchronous and Synchronous) and RTC hour
  32:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         format using the HAL_RTC_Init() function.
  33:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  34:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** RTC Wakeup configuration ***
  35:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================
  36:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  37:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Wakeup Clock source and Counter use the HAL_RTCEx_SetWakeUpTimer()
  38:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function. You can also configure the RTC Wakeup timer with interrupt mode
  39:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         using the HAL_RTCEx_SetWakeUpTimer_IT() function.
  40:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To read the RTC WakeUp Counter register, use the HAL_RTCEx_GetWakeUpTimer()
  41:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  42:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  43:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Outputs configuration ***
  44:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   =============================
  45:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]  The RTC has 2 outputs pins (RTC_OUT1 & RTC_OUT2).
  46:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         To configure the outputs, use the HAL_RTC_Init() function.
  47:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) RTC_OUT1 and RTC_OUT2 which select one of the following two outputs:
  48:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) CALIB: 512Hz or 1Hz clock output (with an LSE frequency of 32.768kHz).
  49:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         To enable the CALIB, use the HAL_RTCEx_SetCalibrationOutPut() function.
  50:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) TAMPALRM: This output is the OR between rtc_tamp_evt and ALARM signals.
  51:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         ALARM is enabled by configuring the OSEL[1:0] bits in the RTC_CR register
  52:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         which select the alarm A, alarm B or wakeup outputs.
  53:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         rtc_tamp_evt is enabled by setting the TAMPOE bit
  54:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         in the RTC_CR register which selects the tamper event outputs.
  55:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  56:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Smooth digital Calibration configuration ***
  57:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================================
  58:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  59:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Configure the RTC Original Digital Calibration Value and the corresponding
  60:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         calibration cycle period (32s,16s and 8s) using the HAL_RTCEx_SetSmoothCalib()
  61:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  62:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  63:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** RTC synchronization ***
  64:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================================
  65:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  66:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The RTC can be finely adjusted using HAL_RTCEx_SetSynchroShift() function.
  67:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         Writing to RTC_SHIFTR can shift (either delay or advance) the clock with
  68:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         a resolution of 1 ck_apre period.
  69:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         The shift operation consists in adding the SUBFS[14:0] value to the synchronous
  70:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         prescaler counter SS[15:0]: this delays the clock.
  71:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  72:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Bypass shadow registers ***
  73:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================================
  74:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  75:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Enable bypass shadow registers using the HAL_RTCEx_EnableBypassShadow().
  76:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         When the Bypass Shadow is enabled the calendar value are taken directly
  77:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         from the Calendar counter.
  78:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         Thus eliminating the need to wait for the RSF bit to be set.
  79:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         This is especially useful after exiting from low-power modes (Stop or Standby),
  80:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         since the shadow registers are not updated during these modes.
  81:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  82:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** RTC ultra-low-power mode ***
  83:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================================
  84:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  85:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Configure the RTC ultra-low-power mode using HAL_RTCEx_SetLowPowerCalib() function.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\DELL\AppData\Local\Temp\ccMtHSyM.s 			page 3


  86:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         In this case, the calibration mechanism is applied on ck_apre instead of RTCCLK.
  87:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         The resulting accuracy is the same, but the calibration is performed during a
  88:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         calibration cycle of about 220 x PREDIV_A x RTCCLK pulses instead of 220 RTCCLK pulses.
  89:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  90:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** RTC subsecond register underflow interruption ***
  91:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================================
  92:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  93:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Enable the RTC SSRU interruption mode using HAL_RTCEx_SetSSRU_IT() function.
  94:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         In this case, when the SSR rolls under 0, an SSRU interruption is triggered.
  95:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         Disable the RTC SSRU interruption mode using HAL_RTCEx_DeactivateSSRU() function.
  96:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
