 114:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    *** Tamper configuration ***
 115:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    ============================
 116:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    [..]
 117:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****      (+) Enable the RTC Tamper and configure the Tamper filter count, trigger Edge
 118:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          or Level according to the Tamper filter (if equal to 0 Edge else Level)
 119:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          value, sampling frequency, NoErase, MaskFlag,  precharge or discharge and
 120:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          Pull-UP using the HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper() function. You can configure RTC Tamper
 121:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          with interrupt mode using HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper_IT() function.
 122:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****      (+) The default configuration of the Tamper erases the backup registers. To avoid
 123:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          erase, enable the NoErase field on the TAMP_CR2 register.
 124:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****      (+) With new RTC tamper configuration, you have to call HAL_RTC_Init() in order to
 125:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          perform TAMP base address offset calculation.
 126:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****      (+) Enable Internal tamper using HAL_RTCEx_SetInternalTamper. IT mode can be chosen using
 127:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          setting Interrupt field.
